<BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR> look guys, here's our main problem in RVR. we run up on a hib or mid group and bam, our 8 gets mez'd first every time... why? insta mez. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Like Uziel said this is one of the mainproblems, not that the pet is week or something. Pets are in generall not that usefull then in PvE. Usually they get mezzed with you and do nothing. You can't send the pet over a rang from 1875 like a theurg can, so a I am usually out of range to bring my pet into play, expect I am soloing a oponent.<P>If I die, and that happens quite often as a caster class in RvR, my pet is lost and then you don't have your privat tank with you anymore. That is why I like Mangos Idea of a spell to rebuild the last Pet. That would make pets more usefull in RvR. Then extend the range where I can send a pet to bolt range. That would allow me to send my pet into a group to confuse them a bit and give me the time to get into AE mezz range. Off course I can still be instant mezzed/stunned what ever, like uziel said...<BR>But independent of what will be changed (I hope so) more points need to be available to spec. Lets say 1.2-1.5 or something like that. This would allow as to make more different variants of the sorc. If I fully spec mind at the moment I get a normal DD not very impressiv. If I do the same with body I get weak Mezz and can't charm L50 pets. I can't get Perfect in at least one line to be good. There is only the 35,34 alternative to make let me be a medium char. Just take some other class, to campare with. Some classes just need to spec one line to be evektiv in RvR or RvE. Take a firewizz, he can spec everything in fire and is nearly done.<P>I have some other idee to make the pet more effektiv in RvR:<BR>What about a spell that let our pet teleport to an oponent on 1875 range with lets say 5-10 minute timer?<P>Ok here is what I would change:<BR>- Change the multiplier from 1.0 to 1.5, that would give us more flexability<BR>- Add a AE Debuff that increases our DD dmg.(why should I want a fire debuff if my own dmg isn't fire dmg?)<BR>- Add a heal/lifetransfer spell for my pet, or increase the HP regeneration (it has extremly low HP regeneration speed)<BR>- Add a "rebuild Pet" spell in the mind line like Manko descriped.<BR>- Add some sort of instant spell that give us some weapon against the oder instant AE spells from hib/mid<BR>- Increase the "send pet" range to 1875 or add the teleport spell or something like this<P>generall:<BR>- perge is a big nerv to all mezzers but I think the RA is not bad only the implementation is, my suggestion is to make it less effectiv.<P>variant 1: (Color = color of the oponent that mezzed you)<BR>Color   - chance that purge works<BR>gray    - 100 % (It should not happen that a gray owns you that would suck extremly)<BR>green  - 83 %<BR>blue    - 67 %<BR>yellow - 50 %<BR>orange - 33 %<BR>red      - 17 %<BR>purple  - 0 %<P>variant 2:<BR>purge level 1 - 10 %<BR>purge level 2 - 20 %<BR>purge level 3 - 30 %<BR>purge level 4 - 40 %<BR>purge level 5 - 50 %<P>variant 3:<BR>a combination of 1 and 2.<BR>gray    - 75 %<BR>green  - 60 %<BR>blue    - 40 %<BR>yellow - 25 %<BR>orange- 17 %<BR>red      - 8 %<BR>purple  - 0 %<P>purge level 1 - 5%<BR>purge level 2 - 10 %<BR>purge level 3 - 15 %<BR>purge level 4 - 20 %<BR>purge level 5 - 25 %<P>The total chance is then a combination of both. Lets say you got purge leve 2 (10%) and you are mezzed by a yellow your chance is 35%.<P>The optimum balanze should be tested out, but the current implementation sounds to strong for me.<P>___________________________________________<P>This changes refer to 1.48 (I am on europe)<BR>___________________________________________<P>--------------------<P>&#8364;XP&#8364;CT TH&#8364; UN&#8364;XP&#8364;CT&#8364;D<P>Beowolve
